The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques in theorem proving, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on the use of deep neural networks (cs.LG) to guide the proof search process of the theorem prover E. The paper also mentions the use of automated theorem provers in program analysis, theory reasoning, security, interpolation, and system verification, which are all subfields of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the formalization and verification of mathematical theorems, which is a subfield of logic (cs.LO) and the use of proof guidance strategies, which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL).
